[White "Standard Tactics"]
[Black "Badmatsyrenov, Oleg vs. Bocharov, Dmitry"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1r3k1/1bqpbppp/p3p3/1p6/1n1BPP2/2NB3R/PPP2QPP/2KR4 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

1. Bxg7 Kxg7 2. Qg3+ Kh8
{ The attempt to flee to the centre would be short-lived:   19...Kf8  20.Rxh7  Bf6  21.e5 !  and Black loses as well. }
3. e5 Nxd3+ 4. Qxd3 f5
{ Things look hopeless for Black, but with this finesse he is able to bring his queen into the defence and prolong the game. }
5. exf6 Qxf4+ 6. Rd2 { 23.Kb1 } 6... Qf5
{ Black has managed to steer the game into a materially more-or-less- equal ending. Nevertheless, this ending is bereft of any chances for him. }
7. Qxf5 exf5 8. fxe7
{ White has an extra pawn and his pieces are much better placed. } 8... Re8
{ 25...Bc6  26.Nd5  Re8  27.Nc7  doesn't give relief either. } 9. Rxd7 Bxg2 10.
Rhd3
{ The pawn on e7 is a monster. White converted in a few more moves and without any real problems. }
