[FEN "2rr2k1/2q1bpp1/p2pbn1p/4p3/2n1P3/2N1BB2/1PP1NPPP/R1QR2K1 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Black's play is mainly on the queenside. These diagrams show two cases where he has already played ...b7-b5 and is using the half-open c-file to create pressure. In some cases he can then use c4 as a springboard for his knight  (shown in the main diagram)  or his rook  (as on the diagram below)  :     White will often be forced to make the weakening pawn move b2-b3.   Model games with this structure:   
Mchedlishvili - Mamedyarov
Vogt - Andersson }
