{ After this move, Black's attack is irresistible, and an attacking maestro like Anand could be relied upon to finish the job.   34.Bxh2  was the damage-limiting move.  Nxh2  Once again,   34...Bxg2 ??  would even lose to  35.Bf4 !  35.Ne4  Now Black has   35.Qxb7  Nxf1  36.Kxf1  Bxc3  37.Rxc3  Qc1+  is losing for White  35...Qd5 !  , with a likely  (but not certain)  win.  If the queen is taken Black has mate in three:   34.Bxg5  Rxg2+  35.Kh1  Rh2+  36.Kg1  Rh1# }
