{ The moment has come for concrete answers from White, because his situation is critical. This is the only move and now the position demands good calculation from both players.  Both sides had seen the possibility of winning the a8-rook, but it was counterproductive for White to indulge himself thus. Here are some cute variations:   25.Qh8+ ?  Ke7  26.Qxa8  Qe3+  27.Rd2   27.Kb1  Qxe2  28.Qxa3  Nxd1  with decisive material gains  27...Qc3+  28.Kb1  A pretty mate motif arises after   28.Rc2  Qa1+  29.Kd2  Ne4+  30.Ke3  Qd4+  31.Kf3  Qf2+  32.Kg4   32.Kxe4  Nc5#  32...f5+  33.gxf6+  Ndxf6+  34.Kh3  Ng5#  Beautiful teamwork between the knight  (s)  and queen !  28...Qxd2  29.Qxa3  Nxh1  Again Black is up a decisive amount of material. }
