[SetUp "1"]

1... Qe4+
{ Giving up the knight for a few checks. White needs to calculate with a little final touch of precision, to see how he can escape from the perpetual.  White has a nice answer if Black tries to arrange mate:   54...Nb3  55.a6  Qe4+  56.Ka2  Qh1  Threatening mate in one. But now there comes  57.Qb7+ !  winning. }
2. Kxc1 Qh1+ 3. Kd2 Qh2+ 4. Ke1
{ White's queen ends up blocking the checks after   57.Ke1  Qh1+  58.Ke2  : for instance,  Qe4+  59.Qe3  Qg2+  60.Qf2  - and now Black's checks are almost at an end.  Qe4+  61.Kd2  Qd3+  62.Kc1 }
