1... Qa7
{ Fischer makes optimal use of all his pieces. The queen threatens to invade on f2 now that the second rank has opened. }
2. Kg2 Ra2
{ Another tricky move for White to face: the threatened ...Rxb2+ would be terminal. }
3. Kf1
{ It is clear that the storm clouds are gathering around the White position, but where is the clincher ?  After   26.Rxa2  Qxa2  27.Re2  Black wins with the obvious  Rxc3 ! }
3... Rxc3
{ The key variations:   26...Rxc3  27.Rxa2   27.bxc3 ?  Qf2#  27...Rf3+  28.Ke2  Rf2+  29.Kd3  Qxa2  .Now the net around the White king is so tight that it has to try and flee alone...  Weirdly,   29...Qc7  threatening mate on c2 also works !  30.Kc3   30.Ra1  Qxb2  -+   30.h4  Rxb2  is also decisive  30...Qxb2+  31.Kb4  Bd2+  ...but in fleeing, White drops a rook  (though doubtless other moves won too.)  32.Kxb5  Bxe1  Here we can end the analysis. }
