1. Rxd6 { The first point. } 1... Qxd6 2. Rxd6 Kxd6
{ At first sight Black seems to be largely unscathed in the short term, but there is a second twist to the combination. }
3. b4 Rc7 4. Qb6+
{ Made possible by that earlier sly sideways slide of the queen to e3. } 4...
Bc6 5. Bh3
{ After   32.Bh3 !  the Black king is in a terminal tangle. The threat is Qc5# and Black must surrender major material to avert it, so rather than play on with the miserable  Rcd7  or something, he chose to resign. }
