1. Rxf7
{ A nice point. White still needs to show something, because he is a rook down. }
1... Kd8 { 28...Kxf7  29.Qg7+  Ke8  30.f7+  is immediately decisive. } 2. Rf8+
Re8 { White is also winning after   29...Be8  30.f7  . } 3. Qg7
{ Threatening a mate in one   Qe7. } 3... Rc7 4. f7
{ Note the major role played by the f-pawn in all these lines ! } 4... Rxf7
