1. Bf6
{ The White player's plan is now about to be completed. She will trade off Black's good dark-squared bishop and thereby free up the f6-square for her knight. Observe how she has brought the weaknesses of Black's king position into sharp focus. }
1... Bg6
{ A nice variation occurs if Black plays   23...Bb7  . The answer then is  24.Bxh8  Rxh8  25.Ng7+  Kd7  Now there comes a beautiful mate, as follows:  or   25...Kd8  26.Qf6+  Qe7  27.Ndxe6+  fxe6  28.Rxd6+  Nd7  29.Nxe6+  Ke8  30.Qg6+  with mate next.  26.Qxf7+ !  Nxf7  27.Rxf7+  Kd8  28.Ndxe6# }
