[Black "Bonus Chapter: Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

{ Hello dear reader !   As we were importing, adjusting and beta-testing Herman Grooten's wonderful book Understanding Before Moving 3: Sicilian Structures Part 1 - Najdorf and Scheveningen, we noticed that in his annotations, the author has often referenced famous  (and less famous)  games which he didn't include in the book.   Considering that the Move Trainer allows linking to specific variations and that almost all beta-testers asked whether it would be possible to include games mentioned by Grooten in the course and link to them in relevant variations.  Initially, the plan was to collect every single game Grooten mentioned. However, after a while, we realized their number is simply overwhelming. If really singled out every game in his notes, we would quickly go over 150, probably even 200.  Therefore, a compromise was made - we have decided to dig up only those games mentioned in the 'Overview' chapters and not those included in notes in 'Model Games' chapters simply because Grooten pointed them out as key theoretical games. As you will notice, their number is quite substantial as it is.  Thus, in this chapter, you will find games Grooten casually mentioned his notes, but that were not included in the book's Model Games chapters.  The games were not annotated, but serve as a reference and you will find links corresponding to them at appropriate places in this course.   We hope it will help you navigate those complicated Sicilian waters and deepen your knowledge of the structures analyzed by Grooten in the book.   Your Chessable team !   April 2020. }
1. -- *

